shared_text:
YOUTUBE.COM
ALA 9/11 Tribute 15 min
text:
Dear parents, students, and friends of ALA;
There are days each year that cause us all to stop and take inventory of our lives and what is really important to each of us. For many of us September 11 is one of those day’s. 19 years ago on that day the world was changed and for many of us time stopped as we contemplate the magnitude and significance of what was happening. America was under attack and our countrymen and women were being killed on American soil. This stark realization unified our country and the people and now September 11 is known as Patriot Day to remember the citizens who acted with bravery and honor while under attack and to remember the Heroic acts by first responders who ran in to harms way to save those who could not run away from the harm. Today we remember and pause and take stock of the freedom that we still have, and to remember the words “In God We Trust”!

https://youtu.be/HFUTFsUwP-o

YOUTUBE.COM
ALA 9/11 Tribute 15 min

post_text:
Big Changes! Beginning with the 2021-2022 academic year, ACT scores will not be used to calculate scholarship awards at Snow College.

While a student may qualify for the Presidential Scholarship based on their GPA, this award is made based on limited funds. We encourage students to apply as early as possible and not wait for College Application Week. The deadline to apply for the Presidential Scholarship is November 30th.

All other awards are not based on limited funding so a student will need to apply by March 1st.

Applications for Snow College open September 14th.

ELEMENTARY BACK TO SCHOOL NIGHT!

It has been an amazing first full week back at school! We have missed all of our wonderful students so much, and we are so happy to have them back with us in school again!

Our first big event of the new school year will be “Back-To-School Night”, which will be held this upcoming Wednesday, August 26th from 5 p.m. to 7 p.m.

We will have three “In-Person” sessions of “Back-To-School Night”. Sessions will be limited to 10 people per classroom. Teachers will send you a link to sign up through Sign Up Genius. Please indicate the number of people who will be attending. We ask that you limit attendance to parents/guardians only so that we can have enough space for social distancing. For those who do not want to attend in person, the teachers will send out a video to all parents/guardians so that you can receive the same information.
We look forward to seeing you!

#hereatala

post_text:
The ALA Choirs will be holding our Boot Camp on August 3rd-5th for all 5th-12th grade students. The High School students in Evolution will also be meeting on Saturday, August 1st from 8am-9pm.

Should you have a 5th grader through 12th grader that would be interested in trying out for one of our three show choirs at ALA: Tyros (Elementary), InPulse (Junior High) and Evolution (High School), the audition will be FRIDAY, JULY 31st in the Jr. High Auditorium, from 8am-9am.

Audition Expectations:
1. Prepare 30 seconds to 1 minute of an uptempo Pop or Broadway Song.
2. Prepare 30 seconds to 1 minute of a slow, heartfelt ballad (We would like these pieces to show contrast).
3. Be prepared to learn a short choreographed sequence that you will be judged on.

Thank you and we are looking forward to your auditions!

If interested in auditioning for a show choir, please email:
Tyros or EVO = rlunt@americanleadership.net
InPulse = jkeith@americanleadership.net

One of our former ALA students, Rebecca Pedersen, is on her way to perform in the Metropolitan Opera in New York.

Rebecca attended ALA all through high school and was an early graduate of the Class of 2010.

She sang in the choir under the direction of Rick Lunt and was in the MDT program with Mrs. Elaine Hansen and Mr. Larry Blackburn. Blackburn states, "I have never seen a person go after their dream like Rebecca has".

She is one of our ALA Eagles that flew and continues to fly surpassing all of her own expectations. Congratulations Rebecca Pedersen.

Check out this interview by BYU Weekly
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=B4Q85G4fQdY

post_text:
I want to give a HUGE shout out to my AMAZING lunch crew at ALA!! Words cannot express how grateful I am for all of you. You guys are outstanding! Thank you for always being willing to go the extra mile for me and our wonderful school. My lunch crew is always ready and willing to try out all of my new ideas, and together we have created miracles. We have spent endless hours together making food for our ALA students and their siblings. We went to great effort to make sure that all of our students felt loved during these times away from school.
I could not run the lunch program without them.
It has been so wonderful to see all of the ways that our school lunches have helped our families.
Thank you again to our ALA families for all of your love and support to our lunch program, and our lunch crew.
We have loved all of the cards, pictures, notes, treats and flowers, home videos and signs from students hanging out their car windows.
It was wonderful!!!!!
Have a happy and safe summer.

Thank you,
Missy Muhlestein
ALA Food Service Director

post_text:
American Leadership Academy would like to recognize the following seniors who fulfilled all the requirements to obtain the Seal of Biliteracy:

Brigitte Lizarraga
Moroni Mendoza
Alvaro Mestre

These students have demonstrated proficiency in the English Language as well as the Spanish language. They are graduating with this Seal, which is going to show in their transcripts and diplomas. This Seal is a recognition from our State Board of Education and will also be recognize by collages and job sites. It means that a bilingual student does not only speak a language other than English, but can read, write and analyze in that language with an intermediate high/advance literacy skills for their age.

#hereatala

post_text:
Thank you is not enough for our amazing lunch team. They continue to show love and support to our students. Often times with encouraging messages, and even coloring/drawing contests. THANK YOU THANK YOU THANK YOU.

"Thank you so much for all that you and your staff have done to give the students a delicious and fun breakfast and lunch each day. My children continue to enjoy the "surprise" each day when we drive to school for lunch. Each day I am amazed at the variety of food you have provided. I imagine most schools are providing sandwiches but my children are receiving such impressive meals. Thank you so much. Please tell express our thanks to your staff. The children also enjoy the slips of paper you include and the sweet notes that are written on the white cartons. So thoughtful!" - Lisa Ro

"Thanks so much for the delicious lunch, fun activity pages and sweet messages! You guys are the best!
Thank you again!" - Heidi Palmer

#hereatala

American Leadership Academy (ALA) - home of the Eagles!

ENROLLING NOW FOR GRADES K-12
801-794-2226 or visit www.americanleadershipacademy.org

"We are excited to have you join us in our 'home of learners', where we believe everyone has the potential to succeed. At ALA, we offer a wide range of academic classes and extracurricular activities, so designed such that there is room for each and every student to excel in his/her own way." -Rich Morley, Director.

One of the top programs at ALA is our amazing nationally ranked show choir programs. Choirs range from 4th grade through high school. And are under the direction of Rick Lunk and Jordan Keith.

Tours are set up by appointment only. email kjames@americanleadership.net or call 801-794-2226 ext. 220

ALA CHOIR AUDITIONS
Online Submissions Due: Tuesday, April 28

The ALA Choir Audition, Online Submissions, for next year's choirs are due on or before Tuesday, April 28. For audition details, information, and processes, go online to (www.alachoir.com).
Current 4th & 5th graders would sign up for Tyros Auditions
Current 6th & 7th graders would sign up for InPulse Auditions
Current 8th - 11th graders would sign up for Evolution Auditions or Concert Choir (if that is their only preference).
Our website contains all of the information needed. However, should you have further questions, please email Mr. Lunt or Mr. Keith.
rlunt@americanleadership.net
jkeith@americanleadership.net

For Further information, check the following website: www.alachoir.com

Please come and join the ALA Choir Legacy!

post_text:
American Leadership Academy is a K-12 tuition free public charter school in Spanish Fork, UT. Our small school has big opportunities for students who want more than a diploma from their educational experience. Dedication to profiding these opportunities is the reason ALA has become a popular alternative to traditional public schools in the area. Students enjoy a 4-day school week, optional Friday activities, after school clubs, leadership training, quality educators, nationally ranked fine arts, USHAA sports, advanced learning classes, and more. Students and parents alike will immediately connect with our community of family. Join us Here At ALA!!!

Enrolling New Students.
www.americanleadershipacademy.org

post_text:
We wanted to share a few resources to help seniors with the college financial aid process during the COVID-19 school closure period:

If a student's parent(s) have experienced job loss or income decrease
· Unfortunately, many families are experiencing unemployment or a decrease in pay at this time. Attached is a flyer instructing students on FAFSA-next-steps if they find themselves in that unfortunate situation.

If a student needs help completing the FAFSA
· UHEAA Outreach is available for FAFSA assistance M-F, 8am-5pm: 801-366-8487/outreach@utahsbr.edu.
· UHEAA’s FAFSA walk-through video demonstrates an entire FAFSA step-by-step for those attempting to complete the FAFSA at home
· UHEAA Outreach will host a Twitter Chat through the @UtahFutures account Friday, April 24 from 1pm-2pm. This is a chance for your students to submit their own questions about the FAFSA and see responses to other commonly-asked FAFSA inquiries.

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gUis5lityCQ&feature=emb_rel_err

If you have any questions, please email jjensen@americanleadership.net

#hereatala

post_text:
Important information on the Coronavirus from the CDC and Utah Department of Health.

The Utah Department of Health is actively monitoring an outbreak caused by a novel (new) coronavirus (COVID-19) first identified in Wuhan, Hubei Province, China. This outbreak began in early December 2019 and continues to expand in China and other countries.
NO CASES HAVE BEEN CONFIRMED IN UTAH. Although, the UDOH has investigated, and ruled out, several potential cases. Only cases diagnosed in Utah will be counted as Utah cases. Utah’s disease surveillance system is working as designed, as public health officials and health care providers are coordinating to identify and investigate potential cases.

While this is a worrisome public health situation, the immediate health risk from COVID-19 to the general public is believed to be low.

Please read through the information, share with friends and family.

Brianna Wells, RN
ALA School Nurse

#hereatala
#HereAtALA

To Parents of 11th grade students,

Starting the week of February 10th, the counselors will be conducting College and Career Readiness meetings with all 11th grade students and parents.

This is a great opportunity for parents to know where your student is, as far as credits and career choices. You will be able to ask questions and get information on your student's future plans.

You can book an appointment with June Jensen by going to the ALA Website. Click on the counselor tab and scroll to "Schedule an Appointment". Appointments are 30 minute increments. If you need more time, please schedule two spots.

2020-2021 K-12 New Student Enrollment Open House at American Leadership Academy.

ALA is a K-12 tuition free public charter school in Spanish Fork. Our small school has big opportunities for students who want more than a diploma from their educational experience. Dedication to providing these opportunities is the reason ALA has become a popular alternative to traditional public schools in the area.

Students enjoy a 4-day school week, optional Friday activities, after school clubs, leadership training, quality educators, nationally recognized fine arts, USHAA sports, advanced learning classes, and more. Students and parents alike will immediately connect with our community of family.

Join us Here At ALA:
January 30th
6-7pm
Jr. High Rotunda

To schedule a school tour, contact Kathy James at 801-794-2226 ext. 220

post_text:
2020-2021 K-12 New Student Enrollment Open House at American Leadership Academy.

ALA is a K-12 tuition free public charter school in Spanish Fork. Our small school has big opportunities for students who want more than a diploma from their educational experience. Dedication to providing these opportunities is the reason ALA has become a popular alternative to traditional public schools in the area.

Students enjoy a 4-day school week, optional Friday activities, after school clubs, leadership training, quality educators, nationally recognized fine arts, USHAA sports, advanced learning classes, and more. Students and parents alike will immediately connect with our community of family.

Join us Here At ALA:
January 30th
6-7pm
Jr. High Rotunda

To schedule a school tour, contact Kathy James at 801-794-2226 ext. 220

WE DID IT!
Congratulations to all who participated in the Make-A-Wish fundraisers.
A total of $2205 dollars was raised in the beard cards, penny wars, dances, and volleyball tournaments. $2505 dollars was raised yesterday in the dress down day for a total of $4710 dollars. Thank you to Chil-Fil-A who will donate the remaining $290 dollars to help Mateo and his family go to Disney World.
#HereAtALA

"The joy of brightening other lives becomes for us the magic of the holidays." W.C. Jones

Christmas Stockings for Senior Citizens 2019

The Elementary school is participating in an initiative lead by our Eagle Council to gather donated items (specifically requested: packages nuts, candy canes, cashews, toothpaste, hats, scarves, gloves, stockings).

A box for donations is in each classroom and at the front desk of the elementary school. Our hope is to gather the items throughout the next couple weeks.

The last day to donate is Monday, December 16th.

#HereAtALA
